content:
My almost 6mo old loves this as an additional learning experience. Screen 
lock is KEY.

I have 2 girls~ 14m and 23m old. Both adore this game, hence 5 stars. Not worth $3 I dont think, though they would beg to differ. However, we all agree and love it regardless...  and yes, would recommend. I'm hoping it will become more worth the cost as it developes and updates. More cutsey animals please! More thsnu bubbles or stars or fireworks. More pink. Pink background looks like shark just fed and needs to be lightened.
Awesome
I would give it a better rating if they stopped asking me to rate it
My 2 year old loves it.
Great app 4 toddlers
Great Baby Stuff

My daughter cannot get enough of this. She is four months old and adores watching the fish swim and when she touches the screen and gets a reaction her little legs will kick and she smiles. This app is excellent for sensory as well as teaching cause and effect.
Love the variety of  fish and the ability to pin!
Had this game since daughter was grabbing and pulling everything she loves it. The ability to lock the screen so its only the game going is great as feature. By far best todler/baby game.
My little on loves this "game".  The screen lock makes it the perfect distraction for 5mins of bathroom alone time or "please be quiet at the doctor's office".

I love this app. My daughter LOVES this app. I've had it since she was 5 months. Once she turned 6 months,  I made the decision to purchase the full game!! She cant get enough of it. But,  where did all of the colors for the background go?
replyContent:
Hi Nikki,
If you've enabled performance boost in the settings - you won't have the background colour options. Just untick the performance boost option to re-enable them. 
Thanks!

content: It's my daughter's favorite game!
My daughter and I have to commute an hour away for my job and her babysitter and this app helps her enjoy the long ride back and forth!! Love and totally worth the buy!!
Worth buying!!
Very cute! My 8 month old loves it!
Perfect! Thank you!
18mth old loves it
Love this app! My grandson loves it thank you

My 5 month old baby is memorized by this app/game. Even when she gets fussy, I let her play with this game ands she calms down right away. I liked this app so much that I wanted to support the developers by purchasing the full "extra" version. Thank you! Would love to see more sensory games that infants would enjoy like this one. :)
She loves to watch them move and I love that it locks my buttons so she's not backing out of it all the time.  I wish more toddler games would do that.
Amazing game loads of fun x
Now she wants to eat the fish. Great dev. Very responsive.
My daughter loves it!
Baby loved it. Some very cool UX mechanics too
